# ============================================================================
# security.list.chroot  --  Corvid OS curated security / pentest tool catalog
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# live-build package list. RULES for this file (do not break them):
#   * ONE package per line.
#   * '#' comments must be on their OWN line -- live-build 3.0 does NOT strip
#     inline comments, so a trailing "pkg  # note" is passed to apt verbatim
#     and BREAKS the build. Every comment here is a full line starting with #.
#
# CURATION APPROACH (why this list looks the way it does)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The base is Kubuntu 24.04 LTS (noble). Every package below was VERIFIED to
# exist in Ubuntu noble main/universe (checked against packages.ubuntu.com on
# 2026-07-04). They install cleanly on the Ubuntu base with NO library skew --
# unlike Parrot/Kali's Debian-built binaries, which drag in glibc/python/lib
# mismatches that break an Ubuntu graft at build time.
#
# This replaces the earlier failed plan of installing Parrot's
# `parrot-tools-full` metapackage: that package is NOT in Parrot's `lory` repo
# (which ships only ~6 core packages), and Parrot's tool binaries conflict with
# the Ubuntu base. So we curate from Ubuntu's OWN universe instead.
#
# KALI-ONLY TOOLS ARE NOT BAKED IN HERE.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Well-known tools that Ubuntu does NOT package (metasploit-framework, seclists,
# exploitdb/searchsploit, the social-engineer-toolkit, crackmapexec/netexec,
# responder, wpscan, sslyze, theHarvester, enum4linux, feroxbuster, volatility3,
# and other Kali-exclusives) are deliberately LEFT OUT of this build. Baking
# Kali packages into the ISO risks the exact library-skew build breakage we are
# avoiding. Instead they are offered on-demand by the RUNTIME INSTALLER, which
# pulls them from the low-priority, pinned Kali fallback repo configured in
# config/archives/kali.list.chroot + kali.pref.chroot. See the commented
# "KALI FALLBACK" catalog at the bottom of this file for the known names.
# ============================================================================


# ============================================================================
# Network discovery & scanning
# ============================================================================
nmap
masscan
netdiscover
arp-scan
fping
hping3
netcat-openbsd
socat
tcpdump
p0f
netsniff-ng

# ============================================================================
# DNS enumeration & host/OSINT recon
# ============================================================================
# dnsutils is the familiar transitional name; bind9-dnsutils is the concrete
# package that ships dig/nslookup/host in noble. Both are kept for safety.
dnsutils
bind9-dnsutils
whois
dnsrecon
dnsenum
fierce
dmitry

