# ============================================================================
# KALI FALLBACK CATALOG  (NOT installed by this list -- reference only)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The names below are the well-known Kali-exclusive tools that are NOT in
# Ubuntu noble (each was checked and returned "No such package" on
# packages.ubuntu.com, 2026-07-04, unless noted as a Go/other upstream-only
# tool). Do NOT uncomment these here -- Kali binaries baked into the ISO can
# break the Ubuntu base. Install them at RUNTIME instead, e.g.:
#     sudo apt update
#     sudo apt install -t kali-rolling metasploit-framework
# apt resolves them from the pinned Kali fallback repo (Pin-Priority 100), while
# every core lib stays on Ubuntu (hard-blocked at -1). See kali.pref.chroot.
#
# Exploitation / frameworks:
#   metasploit-framework
#   exploitdb                 # provides searchsploit; not in noble
#   set                       # social-engineer-toolkit
#   beef-xss
#   commix                    # was in older Ubuntu, dropped from noble
#
# Credential / AD / SMB attack:
#   crackmapexec              # a.k.a. netexec on newer Kali
#   responder
#   enum4linux                # neither enum4linux nor enum4linux-ng is in noble
#
# Web:
#   wpscan
#   feroxbuster
#   skipfish                  # dropped from noble
#
# Recon / OSINT (upstream Go/py tools Ubuntu does not package):
#   theharvester
#   amass
#   subfinder
#   nuclei
#
# TLS / crypto analysis:
#   sslyze
#
# Wireless / RF:
#   kismet                    # dropped from noble
#
# Forensics / memory:
#   volatility3
#   bulk-extractor            # dropped from noble
#
# Wordlists / payloads:
#   seclists
#   wordlists                 # Kali metapackage; no Ubuntu equivalent
#   nishang
#   powersploit
# ============================================================================
